dct_title_s: Worth County, Iowa, 1939, aerial photomosaic index
dct_description_sm: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol CAE. Form of individual image numbering: CAE-1-[number], or CAE-2-[number]. Date of publication inferred from dates on individual photographs within the mosaic. Flown by Aero Service Corp. Philidelphia, Pa. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].
Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
